The authorities mandated to fight corruption in the country have been allocated funds by the National Treasury to boost operations in the 2020/2021 financial year. The Treasury CS Ukur Yatani said that to sustain the fight against corruption, his office has allocated Sh3.1 billion to the Ethics and Anti-Corruption Commission. The same amount has also been proposed to the Office of the Director of Public Prosecutions. While reading his budget estimates to the National Assembly on Thursday, the CS said that his office has proposed an allocation of Sh37.3 billion to Parliament to support its oversight and legislative role. Yatani has also allocated Sh149 million to the Unclaimed Assets Authority and Sh158 million to the Assets and Recovery Agency. The CS has also allocated Sh619.1 million to the Financing Reporting Center. The office of the Director of Criminal Investigations has been allocated Sh7.5 million while the office of the Auditor General has been allocated Sh5.2 million. The Judiciary has been allocated Sh18.1 billion in the 2020/2021 financial year. Yatani proposed Sh10 billion to support unemployed youths through the Kazi Mtaani programme.